      title: 'Warm and Cool Color Collage',
      description: 'Provide magazines, construction paper scraps, and scissors. Label two large poster boards warm colors and cool colors. Discuss which colors are warm like the sun (red, orange, yellow) and which are cool like water (blue, green, purple). Children cut out pictures and paper scraps of each type and glue them onto the correct poster. After the collage, complete a picture-sort worksheet that reinforces the warm-versus-cool classification in printed format.',
